    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** leading the charge at a 71.69 efficiency rating. Despite a stiff matchup against Luis Castillo, **Yordan Alvarez** remains our anchor due to his elite xwOBA (.393) and the inherent value of his spot in the lineup. Similarly, **Trea Turner** (70.89) is a high-priority start; his ability to exploit Pfaadt\u2019s delivery\u2014combined with the bonus points awarded for his leadoff placement\u2014makes him our primary engine for SB production, our most critical category. **Kyle Schwarber** (65.10) also benefits from the Pfaadt matchup, as his elite .402 xwOBA provides significant upside for HR and RBI, compensating for the high-strikeout nature of the opposing pitcher.\n\nOur most tactical decisions revolve around favorable park and platoon shifts. **Jerar Encarnacion** (52.34) sneaks into the starting lineup primarily due to a massive +16% park factor adjustment, while **Hyeseong Kim** (61.56) is a vital start at 2B; his high score is bolstered by a favorable wind-out condition and a slow pitcher delivery that primes him for a potential steal against Jack Leiter. Conversely, **Christian Yelich** (40.14) is a thin start today, suppressed by a daunting matchup against the 2.70 xERA of Foster Griffin and a negative platoon split. He remains in the lineup only because of his projected high floor, but we are monitoring his performance closely.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision involved **Josh Smith**, who finished with a 43.49 score, narrowly missing the cutoff to displace **Dillon Dingler** (46.34) or **Caleb Durbin** (52.26). While **Josh Smith** gained 14% efficiency from a favorable platoon matchup against Emmet Sheehan, the optimizer favored the reliable, albeit lower-ceiling, volume of **Dillon Dingler** in the #4 hole. We continue to hold **Victor Scott II** (36.28) and **Carson Benge** (34.67) on the bench, as their sub-40 scores against tough left-handed pitching keep them below our daily utilization threshold. We remain cautious regarding all lineup-pending statuses, specifically for **Logan O'Hoppe**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Chase Meidroth**, **Caleb Durbin**, **Yordan Alvarez**, **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, **Christian Yelich**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, and **Junior Caminero**, as late adjustments could require a shift in strategy to preserve our limited game caps.",
